Again, I want to say that the order in which it is listed is not important here.

59:41.000 --> 59:45.000
The tasks themselves are important, which we will talk about.

59:45.000 --> 59:50.000
Because for each organization, one or another approach is important,

59:50.000 --> 59:54.000
because everywhere there are weak points, weak places.

59:54.000 --> 59:58.000
So, we usually start with selecting employees and distributing them to work.

59:58.000 --> 01:00:02.000
A person comes to work in an organization.

01:00:02.000 --> 01:00:04.000
This organization already exists.

01:00:04.000 --> 01:00:08.000
Some principles have already developed in this organization, some points.

01:00:08.000 --> 01:00:12.000
It has its own ethics, its own corporate culture.

01:00:12.000 --> 01:00:16.000
If this is a giving organization, then a person comes to work.

01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:22.000
Therefore, this organization is created for some goals, for some tasks.

01:00:22.000 --> 01:00:27.000
And it is created in the way that its owner has.

01:00:27.000 --> 01:00:34.000
As for this selection, it is natural that it is necessary to develop assessment tools.

01:00:35.000 --> 01:00:41.000
The assessment tools of an employee are needed in order to assess his ability,

01:00:41.000 --> 01:00:47.000
assess his competence, conduct his attestation and, accordingly,

01:00:47.000 --> 01:00:50.000
make a certain career trajectory.

01:00:50.000 --> 01:00:55.000
How can an employee advance further in this organization?

01:00:55.000 --> 01:00:57.000
What are his career prospects?

01:00:57.000 --> 01:01:00.000
What are his career tasks?

01:01:00.000 --> 01:01:03.000
What goals can he have in this organization?

01:01:03.000 --> 01:01:08.000
In addition to the fact that, of course, he performs the functionality that is assigned to him,

01:01:08.000 --> 01:01:11.000
according to the vacancy that he occupies.

01:01:13.000 --> 01:01:21.000
In addition, the theory of organizational behavior should take care of the validity of the tools

01:01:21.000 --> 01:01:23.000
that are used to solve these tasks.

01:01:23.000 --> 01:01:28.000
A large number of tests have been developed today, which we have already talked about.

01:01:28.000 --> 01:01:33.000
But these tests, which were developed during and after the Second World War,

01:01:33.000 --> 01:01:38.000
were characterized by the fact that they were tested on a huge number of people.

01:01:38.000 --> 01:01:41.000
Millions of people took these tests.

01:01:41.000 --> 01:01:45.000
Modern tests are developed, unfortunately, very quickly,

01:01:45.000 --> 01:01:48.000
and the issue of their adaptation is not paid enough attention.

01:01:50.000 --> 01:01:56.000
In this regard, there is a problem of how valid these tests are.

01:01:56.000 --> 01:02:01.000
Unfortunately, very often, a lot of attention is paid to these tests,

01:02:01.000 --> 01:02:09.000
and it is believed that these tests allow a person to get all the information that he hides

01:02:09.000 --> 01:02:12.000
or that he does not want to demonstrate.

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:15.000
And, of course, if we choose from such parcels,

01:02:15.000 --> 01:02:19.000
then we will have our own attitude to the results that we receive.

01:02:19.000 --> 01:02:27.000
In order not to make a mistake, in order not to miss a really necessary person

01:02:27.000 --> 01:02:32.000
who will be useful in our work, it is necessary to ask the question of validity.

01:02:32.000 --> 01:02:37.000
No matter how understandable, pleasant and obvious the test is,

01:02:37.000 --> 01:02:41.000
the main task is not in this, but in the fact that it is really valid,

01:02:41.000 --> 01:02:44.000
that it is reliable and that it is tested on a large number of people,

01:02:44.000 --> 01:02:51.000
that it really solves the tasks that have been created and meets the requirements that are presented to it.

01:02:52.000 --> 01:02:59.000
The next task that is solved in the same area is the professional analysis.

01:02:59.000 --> 01:03:06.000
A person comes with certain knowledge and corresponds to a certain profession.

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:11.000
He can correspond to it successfully, he can correspond to it unsuccessfully.

01:03:11.000 --> 01:03:16.000
He may require additional knowledge, and therefore the question arises

01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:23.000
whether we should pre-educate a person, or we should re-educate him,

01:03:23.000 --> 01:03:28.000
or a person can correspond to another professional area,

01:03:28.000 --> 01:03:31.000
whether in our organization or not.

01:03:31.000 --> 01:03:38.000
But here it is necessary to conduct an analysis of how much a person meets the professional requirements

01:03:38.000 --> 01:03:43.000
that are presented to him at his new workplace.

01:03:43.000 --> 01:03:48.000
At the same time, the development and application of the personnel selection program

01:03:48.000 --> 01:03:53.000
becomes of great importance in this respect.

01:03:53.000 --> 01:03:57.000
In large modern companies, they have long moved away from the situation

01:03:57.000 --> 01:04:01.000
that they take a person from the street and then try to teach him.

01:04:02.000 --> 01:04:09.000
Now the company is interested in hiring experts,

01:04:09.000 --> 01:04:14.000
in this regard, there are various kinds of contracts with universities,

01:04:14.000 --> 01:04:19.000
corporate universities are being created, business centers are being created,

01:04:19.000 --> 01:04:22.000
corporate educational centers are being created,

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:29.000
which solve the task of assigning the employee the necessary knowledge,

01:04:29.000 --> 01:04:33.000
training and development of the necessary competencies,

01:04:33.000 --> 01:04:38.000
which will be useful for solving the tasks that will be presented to him.

01:04:38.000 --> 01:04:46.000
At the same time, the task of optimizing the placement of the personnel becomes of great importance.

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:53.000
We have already talked about the fact that modern organizations are not a rigid structure

01:04:53.000 --> 01:04:55.000
that will exist for decades.

01:04:55.000 --> 01:04:59.000
Modern organizations, whether they are theoretical or matric,

01:04:59.000 --> 01:05:05.000
very often create working groups to solve a particular task.

01:05:05.000 --> 01:05:09.000
They are called in different ways, working group, project group,

01:05:09.000 --> 01:05:14.000
design group, development group, temporary group.

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:20.000
This is a group of employees, a group of departments,

01:05:20.000 --> 01:05:24.000
which are created specifically to solve a particular task.

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:27.000
Very often, people are selected for the solution of a particular task.

01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:31.000
And then the task arises, the question arises, here the task is solved.

01:05:31.000 --> 01:05:36.000
How optimal are these employees for working in this organization?

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:43.000
Should they be fired or should they be transferred to another field of activity?

01:05:43.000 --> 01:05:49.000
How will they be able to solve certain tasks?

01:05:49.000 --> 01:05:51.000
This is a problem of optimization.

01:05:51.000 --> 01:05:54.000
We have already invested funds in these specialists.

01:05:54.000 --> 01:05:57.000
We have already provided them with work and training.

01:05:57.000 --> 01:06:05.000
Therefore, now the task arises for these employees to be optimal

01:06:05.000 --> 01:06:08.000
in terms of the tasks that are created by the organization.

01:06:08.000 --> 01:06:13.000
Pay attention, it is the organization, because the organization has a priority

01:06:13.000 --> 01:06:18.000
in the face of the needs and needs of the employees.

01:06:19.000 --> 01:06:25.000
At the same time, it is necessary to solve the task of forming a personnel reserve.

01:06:25.000 --> 01:06:30.000
The fact is that if an employee has worked in an organization for a long time,

01:06:30.000 --> 01:06:34.000
he already knows its corporate culture, its tasks.

01:06:34.000 --> 01:06:40.000
He already knows and accepts the psychological climate,

01:06:40.000 --> 01:06:44.000
the psychological norms, the psychological background that arises in him.

01:06:45.000 --> 01:06:51.000
In this regard, the problem arises that the promotion of this employee

01:06:51.000 --> 01:06:55.000
becomes a bearer of corporate standards.

01:06:55.000 --> 01:07:00.000
He has gone from a manager to a senior manager,

01:07:00.000 --> 01:07:04.000
and now he can already be a manager.

01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:09.000
Now he is in a state of training, guidance, assessment,

01:07:10.000 --> 01:07:14.000
and the formation of work for the new employees.

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:18.000
These are the so-called bearers of organizational experience,

01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:22.000
