01:07:22.000 --> 01:07:28.000
This is the area of tasks that is solved in terms of selecting employees

01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:34.000
and their distribution to work in terms of organizational behavior theory.

01:07:34.000 --> 01:07:39.000
The next area is very important, which we have already mentioned several times today.

01:07:39.000 --> 01:07:43.000
It is training and development of the staff.

01:07:43.000 --> 01:07:49.000
Indeed, tasks are constantly changing, requirements are constantly changing,

01:07:49.000 --> 01:07:52.000
innovations are entering our lives.

01:07:52.000 --> 01:07:57.000
Therefore, we, having employees who occupy their workplaces,

01:07:57.000 --> 01:08:01.000
must pay attention to their development and training.

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:04.000
But this is, of course, investment.

01:08:04.000 --> 01:08:06.000
Moreover, investment is not small.

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:10.000
If we look at the modern educational service market,

01:08:10.000 --> 01:08:15.000
there are a large number of providers that offer different trainings,

01:08:15.000 --> 01:08:17.000
different training programs.

01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:20.000
They are of different cost, they have different prices,

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:23.000
but at the same time they have different reputations.

01:08:23.000 --> 01:08:30.000
Therefore, the problem arises with which providers the contracts are concluded,

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:34.000
with which providers to communicate reliably.

01:08:34.000 --> 01:08:39.000
Therefore, it is necessary to determine, first of all, the need for development.

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:42.000
Again, we should not put out the current fire.

01:08:42.000 --> 01:08:47.000
If it suddenly became clear to us that we do not have enough specialists with the necessary knowledge,

01:08:47.000 --> 01:08:51.000
then it is pointless to solve the problem right now.

01:08:51.000 --> 01:08:54.000
This problem could have been foreseen,

01:08:54.000 --> 01:08:59.000
because it was possible to send employees to improve their qualifications in advance,

01:08:59.000 --> 01:09:04.000
without interruption from production, in a certain order,

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:10.000
so that when new tasks arise, we already have trained employees.

01:09:10.000 --> 01:09:14.000
Business always works on foreseeing the situation.

01:09:14.000 --> 01:09:20.000
If you can foresee it successfully, you can successfully get dividends, results,

01:09:20.000 --> 01:09:27.000
bypass competitors and take the leading positions in the niche that is relevant today.

01:09:27.000 --> 01:09:32.000
Therefore, to determine the need for training is not an easy task,

01:09:32.000 --> 01:09:36.000
which is done by specialists in the theory of organizational behavior,

01:09:36.000 --> 01:09:38.000
because, again, the task is risky.

01:09:38.000 --> 01:09:42.000
After all, such specialists may be needed, and they may not be needed.

01:09:42.000 --> 01:09:48.000
Again, we need analytics, again, we need deep knowledge and analysis of the market in which we function.

01:09:49.000 --> 01:09:52.000
After we have determined the need for training,

01:09:52.000 --> 01:09:58.000
it is necessary to compose, approve and agree on the training program.

01:09:58.000 --> 01:10:00.000
Providers have typical training programs.

01:10:00.000 --> 01:10:03.000
We work in a specific company, in a specific organization,

01:10:03.000 --> 01:10:12.000
and therefore it is very important for us to reflect the specific goals, tasks, and needs of our organization.

01:10:12.000 --> 01:10:16.000
We do not need to know the theory of sales at all.

01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:18.000
Open the textbook and read.

01:10:18.000 --> 01:10:26.000
We are interested in the theory of sales of IT equipment, if we work in the corresponding company.

01:10:26.000 --> 01:10:33.000
We are interested in the sales of software, if we work in the corresponding company.

01:10:33.000 --> 01:10:37.000
We are interested in the sales of cars, if we work in a car company, and so on.

01:10:38.000 --> 01:10:42.000
Any training should be specific.

01:10:42.000 --> 01:10:46.000
And it is for specific training that we must pay.

01:10:46.000 --> 01:10:51.000
But here again it is necessary to take into account that in addition to the substantive training,

01:10:51.000 --> 01:10:57.000
it is also necessary to develop management skills, managerial skills.

01:10:57.000 --> 01:11:05.000
Because these are the skills that are associated with the successful construction of the hierarchy of our organization,

01:11:05.000 --> 01:11:11.000
with the successful distribution of authority and responsibilities, with the ability to manage.

01:11:11.000 --> 01:11:18.000
A competent management is a huge need and a huge need for successful business functioning.

01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:24.000
After the needs are determined, the programs are agreed and approved,

01:11:24.000 --> 01:11:29.000
it is necessary to assess the effectiveness of the training.

01:11:29.000 --> 01:11:31.000
This is a very important task.

01:11:31.000 --> 01:11:39.000
Because, indeed, you can send employees to study, you can invest in this means, but the question arises,

01:11:39.000 --> 01:11:48.000
how effective is the training that is happening for this organization?

01:11:48.000 --> 01:11:54.000
So that the training does not turn into training for the sake of training.

01:11:54.000 --> 01:11:59.000
In business, it is still important to solve the tasks that are in front of the organization.

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:05.000
And in this regard, it is necessary to assess the effectiveness of the invested funds and the result.

01:12:05.000 --> 01:12:10.000
If we invest funds, but the result is not there, then it makes you think,

01:12:10.000 --> 01:12:15.000
whether we are teaching them, whether we are teaching them, and whether we are teaching them.

01:12:15.000 --> 01:12:20.000
And just all those tasks that specialists in the theory of organization should analyze and solve.

01:12:20.000 --> 01:12:25.000
Of course, in a significant way, these tasks are solved by HR specialists.

01:12:25.000 --> 01:12:31.000
But we have already talked about the fact that the HR field and the theory of organization are very closely intertwined.

01:12:31.000 --> 01:12:36.000
Maybe closer than other disciplines, which we talked about at the very beginning.

01:12:36.000 --> 01:12:43.000
If we train an employee, then we are interested in the fact that he worked in our company.

01:12:43.000 --> 01:12:50.000
If we invest funds in him, we are interested in the fact that the training that is taking place will benefit the company.

01:12:50.000 --> 01:12:57.000
And therefore, we should be interested in the planning of the career of this employee in our organization.

01:12:57.000 --> 01:13:04.000
If we train an employee, if he is successful, if he grows with the company,

01:13:04.000 --> 01:13:08.000
then we can think about the career growth of this employee.

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:12.000
Maybe he will become a new manager, a new leader.

01:13:12.000 --> 01:13:17.000
After all, the most valuable are those leaders who have passed the whole stage and the entire hierarchy,

01:13:17.000 --> 01:13:20.000
starting from the ground and ending at the highest level.

01:13:20.000 --> 01:13:27.000
They know many underwater stones, they know all the difficulties that arise, they know where and what to pay attention to.

01:13:27.000 --> 01:13:34.000
Therefore, planning a career is a very significant aspect of the theory of organization.

01:13:34.000 --> 01:13:41.000
If an employee knows that his career is planned, he will be interested in working in this particular company.

01:13:41.000 --> 01:13:49.000
Because here he not only receives money, but also carries out personal development and professional growth.

01:13:49.000 --> 01:14:01.000
The next aspect, which is also important in organizational behavior, is organizational development.

01:14:01.000 --> 01:14:05.000
We have already discussed that modern organizations are very mobile.

01:14:05.000 --> 01:14:11.000
In principle, if today the organization is static, it is doomed.

01:14:11.000 --> 01:14:15.000
To a large extent, this is due to the state sector.

01:14:15.000 --> 01:14:26.000
The state sector is very well bureaucratized, but that is why it often does not keep up with the realities that are happening.

01:14:27.000 --> 01:14:38.000
It is here that different business organizations have a significant advantage in terms of the functioning of their actions in the commercial sector.

01:14:38.000 --> 01:14:46.000
But in order to plan organizational development, it is necessary to analyze the structure of the organization.

01:14:46.000 --> 01:14:53.000
Maybe the structure of the organization was very successful a year, two, three, five years ago,

01:14:53.000 --> 01:15:01.000
when the organization was being created, when it actively pushed its market share and when it received the desired results.

01:15:01.000 --> 01:15:05.000
But time has changed, and the structure remains the same.

01:15:05.000 --> 01:15:16.000
If we take the long-term existence of the organization, we can see that the structural units are changing with great difficulty.

01:15:16.000 --> 01:15:24.000
It is very difficult to reduce the existing ones, and even more difficult to create new ones.

01:15:24.000 --> 01:15:36.000
This is often a problem related to large organizations, because they have a branched structure that has already recommended itself.

01:15:36.000 --> 01:15:38.000
People are already working there.

01:15:38.000 --> 01:15:50.000
Accordingly, if we make a reorganization or reduction, then very often we cut people alive, and the problem arises as to how optimal and useful it is.

01:15:50.000 --> 01:15:59.000
Before taking any action, it is necessary to analyze the structure of the organization, how it meets modern needs,

01:15:59.000 --> 01:16:05.000
how much it admires the tasks that may arise in the near future,

01:16:05.000 --> 01:16:11.000
based on the fact that business is constantly changing and new roles and tasks are emerging.

01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:19.000
The next question, which is related to organizational development, is how to increase the satisfaction of employees with work,

01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:24.000
and at the same time, this must be done in order to increase the effectiveness of their work.

01:16:25.000 --> 01:16:33.000
We have already discussed that if a person works for a long time, and this work leads to routine activities,

01:16:33.000 --> 01:16:40.000
he loses interest, he loses attention, and a person becomes interested in further development,

01:16:40.000 --> 01:16:44.000
further developing his career, further developing his personal growth.

01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:47.000
Can this be done in the same organization? It can be done in another.

01:16:47.000 --> 01:16:55.000
So, organizational development is about providing a person who has already gained experience in this organization

01:16:55.000 --> 01:17:01.000
with an opportunity to further develop within the framework of the same organization.

01:17:03.000 --> 01:17:09.000
After the analysis of the structure of the organization is made,

01:17:10.000 --> 01:17:15.000
the assumption is made about the increase in the satisfaction and effectiveness of work,

01:17:15.000 --> 01:17:21.000
the most difficult stage is coming, perhaps, the implementation of the organizational changes themselves.

01:17:21.000 --> 01:17:30.000
Because here, if we make these changes, then we take responsibility for the structure and functioning of a successful organization,

01:17:30.000 --> 01:17:36.000
and for the fate of those people who work in this organization and whom we change,

01:17:36.000 --> 01:17:39.000
because we make some changes.

01:17:39.000 --> 01:17:42.000
Changes are always perceived by a person in a painful way.

01:17:42.000 --> 01:17:46.000
There is something that I am already used to, and I know what I can learn from it.

01:17:46.000 --> 01:17:48.000
And little or nothing will happen now.

01:17:48.000 --> 01:17:50.000
And these are the restrictions that are being imposed.

01:17:50.000 --> 01:17:55.000
Maybe this is an attempt to get rid of me, to reduce me, to fire me, and so on.

01:17:55.000 --> 01:18:00.000
Organizational development is a very significant layer of organizational behavior,

01:18:00.000 --> 01:18:06.000
because development is usually faced with a counteraction to this development.

01:18:06.000 --> 01:18:09.000
How to make it the most painless?

01:18:09.000 --> 01:18:17.000
How to help this organizational change and further contribute to the effectiveness of the organization,

01:18:17.000 --> 01:18:23.000
contribute to the development of organizational behavior in a progressive direction,

01:18:23.000 --> 01:18:26.000
but not from the point of view of sabotage or regression.

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:38.000
The next big direction that can be highlighted in organizational behavior is the measurement of the work.

01:18:38.000 --> 01:18:44.000
Business is always a matter of calculation, a matter of quantity.

01:18:44.000 --> 01:18:49.000
And we always know how much we produce, what we produce, how we produce.

01:18:49.000 --> 01:18:58.000
We plan, and planning is an important element, the number of staff to produce certain products,

01:18:58.000 --> 01:19:04.000
to provide certain services, to cover the entire market sector.

01:19:04.000 --> 01:19:12.000
In this regard, before performing certain results, before performing organizational measurements,

01:19:13.000 --> 01:19:18.000
before performing organizational development, before performing training, selection of employees,

01:19:18.000 --> 01:19:26.000
it is necessary to find out how and whether we consider certain results to be correct.

01:19:26.000 --> 01:19:31.000
Naturally, when it comes to measurements, the first thing to do is to develop criteria.

01:19:31.000 --> 01:19:34.000
What exactly are we going to measure?

01:19:34.000 --> 01:19:39.000
The number of products, the number of dismissals, the number of missed working days,

01:19:39.000 --> 01:19:45.000
the number of horizontal and vertical movements, the number of material stimuli,

01:19:45.000 --> 01:19:48.000
the number of employees to be trained, and so on.

01:19:48.000 --> 01:19:52.000
We must discuss the criteria that we will measure.

01:19:52.000 --> 01:19:54.000
Because you can measure anything.

01:19:54.000 --> 01:20:02.000
The question is how significant these criteria are in order to solve the development tasks

01:20:02.000 --> 01:20:05.000
that are before our particular organization.

01:20:06.000 --> 01:20:14.000
Again, after we have developed these criteria, it is necessary to determine whether each of these criteria is useful.

01:20:14.000 --> 01:20:20.000
Are all these criteria really significant or are they secondary?

01:20:20.000 --> 01:20:25.000
Naturally, it is obvious that by increasing the salary, people will be satisfied.

01:20:25.000 --> 01:20:32.000
The whole question is what is the ratio of salary increase and labor productivity.

01:20:32.000 --> 01:20:37.000
Let's recall the same Khatunov experiments with informal relations.

01:20:37.000 --> 01:20:42.000
Let's recall the same Taylor with his scientific organization of labor.

01:20:42.000 --> 01:20:47.000
Indeed, material stimulation is good to a certain extent.

01:20:47.000 --> 01:20:52.000
But when these limits are reached,

01:20:52.000 --> 01:21:00.000
then material stimulation no longer significantly affects any result.

01:21:00.000 --> 01:21:08.000
Therefore, it is necessary to analyze the importance and significance of the criteria we have set.

01:21:08.000 --> 01:21:12.000
This is another task, and the task is no less important than the development of the criteria themselves.

01:21:12.000 --> 01:21:18.000
The next task is to assess the efficiency of the organization.

01:21:18.000 --> 01:21:22.000
We believe that the organization is effective.

01:21:22.000 --> 01:21:27.000
We believe that the organization covers a large segment of the market, that the profit is growing.

01:21:27.000 --> 01:21:29.000
Is the organization effective?

01:21:29.000 --> 01:21:35.000
Maybe it is not an intensive, but an extensive growth.

01:21:35.000 --> 01:21:41.000
The organization really increases the profit due to quantitative indicators.

01:21:41.000 --> 01:21:46.000
We already know and consider that quantitative indicators are good for a certain approach.

01:21:46.000 --> 01:21:53.000
In the end, you can produce a huge number of aluminum spoons,

01:21:53.000 --> 01:21:57.000
but, accordingly, these spoons will not be in demand.

01:21:57.000 --> 01:22:01.000
Accordingly, the organization will lose its effectiveness.

01:22:01.000 --> 01:22:06.000
This is a huge problem for all Soviet organizations,

01:22:06.000 --> 01:22:11.000
which collapsed in the 1990s.

01:22:11.000 --> 01:22:16.000
They were ineffective because they produced the product that was not in demand.

01:22:16.000 --> 01:22:22.000
They produced products that were not in demand.

01:22:22.000 --> 01:22:25.000
They were bought because there was nothing.

01:22:25.000 --> 01:22:30.000
But when something else appeared, all these enterprises stopped.

01:22:30.000 --> 01:22:36.000
Not because they became financed, but simply because their products turned out to be of no use to anyone.

01:22:36.000 --> 01:22:41.000
They lost in the competitive struggle that began.

01:22:41.000 --> 01:22:50.000
The next direction that must be highlighted in the system of organizational behavior

01:22:50.000 --> 01:22:57.000
is the analysis of the quality of life of employees.

01:22:57.000 --> 01:23:03.000
We spend at least a third of our working life.

01:23:03.000 --> 01:23:05.000
We sleep almost as much as we do.

01:23:05.000 --> 01:23:08.000
In this regard, the question arises.

01:23:08.000 --> 01:23:16.000
A person comes to work only to work and run away as soon as possible,

01:23:16.000 --> 01:23:19.000
or a person comes to work with an interest.

01:23:19.000 --> 01:23:24.000
This is the same problem that Taylor talked about,

01:23:24.000 --> 01:23:31.000
which was very well formulated by Mayor Ed Lisberger of the informal organization Psychological Climate.

01:23:31.000 --> 01:23:39.000
If a person feels satisfied, if he has a well-developed motivation,

01:23:39.000 --> 01:23:43.000
which will be clear in the theory of motivation,

01:23:43.000 --> 01:23:47.000
then, accordingly, the productivity of labor increases.

01:23:47.000 --> 01:23:53.000
So, accordingly, we need to think about why the productivity of individual workers increases,

01:23:53.000 --> 01:23:56.000
what needs to be done to increase this productivity,

01:23:56.000 --> 01:23:58.000
why the productivity of other workers decreases,

01:23:58.000 --> 01:24:03.000
how to put an end to the decline in the productivity of labor

01:24:03.000 --> 01:24:07.000
and, accordingly, again, to contribute to the growth of this productivity.

01:24:07.000 --> 01:24:12.000
We need to identify factors that are associated with the satisfaction of work.

01:24:12.000 --> 01:24:13.000
What are they?

01:24:13.000 --> 01:24:20.000
Material stimuli, non-material stimuli, literacy, people I work with,

01:24:20.000 --> 01:24:23.000
the style of management that is carried out,

01:24:23.000 --> 01:24:28.000
when I am evaluated as a specialist, when my opinion is considered.

01:24:28.000 --> 01:24:35.000
And in this case, I can agree even on a lower salary than my competitors,

01:24:35.000 --> 01:24:37.000
but there will be a different attitude to me.

01:24:38.000 --> 01:24:45.000
Accordingly, if we identify these factors that are associated with the inner satisfaction of labor,

01:24:45.000 --> 01:24:51.000
then, accordingly, they will be directly associated with the growth of the efficiency of the organization's productivity.

01:24:51.000 --> 01:24:57.000
If we conduct an analysis of the quality of working life,

01:24:57.000 --> 01:25:01.000
then we can think about re-planning of working time.

01:25:01.000 --> 01:25:06.000
What did, in fact, Rettlisberger and Dixon do in their experiments?

01:25:06.000 --> 01:25:12.000
They, from a scientific point of view, simply took the working time

01:25:12.000 --> 01:25:14.000
and, as a designer, cut it down.

01:25:14.000 --> 01:25:19.000
When they took a rest, when they took breaks, when they took lunch.

01:25:19.000 --> 01:25:25.000
But, in fact, if other workers from the control group came to work,

01:25:25.000 --> 01:25:32.000
sat and worked, then the workers in the experimental group felt the attention to themselves.

01:25:33.000 --> 01:25:37.000
And here the re-planning itself was an important element.

01:25:37.000 --> 01:25:39.000
How much is the attitude to them?

01:25:39.000 --> 01:25:42.000
But the very structure of the re-planning was also important.

01:25:42.000 --> 01:25:45.000
The same lunches, the same breaks.

01:25:45.000 --> 01:25:50.000
When they were done according to scientific indicators,

01:25:50.000 --> 01:25:54.000
when the girls were really tired, when the number of mistakes increased,

01:25:54.000 --> 01:25:56.000
and it was necessary to rest,

01:25:57.000 --> 01:26:03.000
then the rest hour was much more successful and much more effective.

01:26:05.000 --> 01:26:13.000
The next important direction, which is considered in the theory of organizational behavior,

01:26:13.000 --> 01:26:16.000
is the analysis of the psychology of consumers.

01:26:16.000 --> 01:26:22.000
Here is a very clear connection with the psychology of consumers of products.

01:26:22.000 --> 01:26:26.000
Look, in fact, everything we have talked about so far

01:26:26.000 --> 01:26:30.000
was about the effectiveness of human behavior in the organization.

01:26:30.000 --> 01:26:33.000
The effectiveness of either the producer of the product,

01:26:33.000 --> 01:26:37.000
or the producer of services.

01:26:37.000 --> 01:26:42.000
But we just talked about the fact that the modern organization,

01:26:42.000 --> 01:26:46.000
the modern paradigm of organizational behavior is associated with the fact

01:26:46.000 --> 01:26:51.000
that the production of a product is inferior to the production of services.

01:26:51.000 --> 01:26:56.000
The service is what I provide to others for consumption.

01:26:56.000 --> 01:27:00.000
Therefore, it is very important for me to know the psychology of consumers.

01:27:00.000 --> 01:27:02.000
As for the psychology of consumers,

01:27:02.000 --> 01:27:09.000
perhaps this is really the novelty that has brought modern development of business.

01:27:09.000 --> 01:27:13.000
This is the modern state of the theory of organizational behavior.

01:27:13.000 --> 01:27:16.000
Because to a large extent,

01:27:16.000 --> 01:27:23.000
we must take into account the needs of those consumers of services or products we work on.

01:27:23.000 --> 01:27:28.000
Here it is necessary to assess the preferences of consumers.

01:27:28.000 --> 01:27:30.000
What is their demand?

01:27:30.000 --> 01:27:32.000
This is where we can work ahead.

01:27:32.000 --> 01:27:35.000
And this is very important from the point of view of services.

01:27:35.000 --> 01:27:39.000
You can offer people something.

01:27:39.000 --> 01:27:41.000
For example, the same tour operators.

01:27:41.000 --> 01:27:44.000
But where do these tour trips go?

01:27:44.000 --> 01:27:46.000
To Turkey, to Egypt.

01:27:46.000 --> 01:27:49.000
Where does the trend go?

01:27:49.000 --> 01:27:53.000
If we assess the preferences of consumers through psychological research,

01:27:53.000 --> 01:27:55.000
analysis, surveys,

01:27:55.000 --> 01:28:01.000
then we can predict and determine the market segment,

01:28:01.000 --> 01:28:03.000
which is still free,

01:28:03.000 --> 01:28:07.000
just because no one has done it before.

01:28:07.000 --> 01:28:15.000
At the same time, it is very important to determine the reaction of consumers to the products offered again.

01:28:15.000 --> 01:28:22.000
Today, the industry produces a huge number of equipment,

01:28:22.000 --> 01:28:27.000
video, computer, audio, household appliances.

01:28:27.000 --> 01:28:30.000
They have a lot of opportunities.

01:28:30.000 --> 01:28:35.000
But the more of these opportunities, the more difficult it is to use this equipment.

01:28:35.000 --> 01:28:39.000
Where is the limit that will be interesting to the consumer?

01:28:39.000 --> 01:28:44.000
You can buy a washing machine, where a huge number of functions are laid.

01:28:44.000 --> 01:28:49.000
But at the same time, such a thick instruction is attached to this washing machine.

01:28:49.000 --> 01:28:51.000
And let's read it, do not understand.

01:28:51.000 --> 01:28:56.000
There are a huge number of good foreign cars today,

01:28:56.000 --> 01:29:00.000
which have a steering memory

01:29:00.000 --> 01:29:04.000
and a variety of automatic movements,

01:29:04.000 --> 01:29:08.000
which the consumer does not know about.

01:29:08.000 --> 01:29:12.000
And as he sat behind the wheel and drove, so he drives.

01:29:12.000 --> 01:29:15.000
Both on a Land Rover and on a Zaporozhets.

01:29:15.000 --> 01:29:17.000
But the opportunities are different.

01:29:17.000 --> 01:29:21.000
So what is the reaction of consumers to these new opportunities?

01:29:21.000 --> 01:29:24.000
After all, every new opportunity makes the product more expensive.

01:29:24.000 --> 01:29:25.000
Where is this limit?

01:29:25.000 --> 01:29:27.000
The ratio, the price, the quality.

01:29:27.000 --> 01:29:30.000
These are the reactions of consumers that also need to be studied.

01:29:30.000 --> 01:29:34.000
And this is the big area that is studied with marketing.

01:29:34.000 --> 01:29:39.000
Consumer psychology is the section where the theory of organization directly correlates

01:29:39.000 --> 01:29:44.000
with both psychology and marketing, when it comes to consumer analysis.

01:29:44.000 --> 01:29:48.000
In marketing, the consumer is one of the leading figures.

01:29:48.000 --> 01:29:52.000
Again, if we talk about consumers,

01:29:52.000 --> 01:29:56.000
then we can develop a strategy for segmenting the market.

01:29:56.000 --> 01:30:00.000
We have identified the potential needs that exist.

01:30:00.000 --> 01:30:03.000
We have identified the ratio that exists.

01:30:03.000 --> 01:30:08.000
And so we can offer what will really be in demand

01:30:08.000 --> 01:30:14.000
according to the price that is now being considered for this product, for these services.

01:30:14.000 --> 01:30:17.000
Thus, we again push the market segment,

01:30:17.000 --> 01:30:20.000
and we are effective from the point of view of business.

01:30:20.000 --> 01:30:24.000
You can talk a lot about consumer psychology.

01:30:24.000 --> 01:30:26.000
This is a separate topic.

01:30:26.000 --> 01:30:31.000
But the main thing that we need now in the theory of organization

01:30:31.000 --> 01:30:35.000
is to understand that the psychology of consumers is a very significant feature

01:30:35.000 --> 01:30:39.000
that must be remembered for the effectiveness of the organization's work.

01:30:39.000 --> 01:30:44.000
Finally, when we talk about organizational behavior,

01:30:44.000 --> 01:30:50.000
such a serious area as engineering psychology stands out.

01:30:50.000 --> 01:31:00.000
We have already talked about this in part when we talked about the development of the theory of organizational behavior after the war.

01:31:00.000 --> 01:31:04.000
Today, technology is becoming very complicated,

01:31:04.000 --> 01:31:06.000
the means of production are becoming more complicated,

01:31:06.000 --> 01:31:08.000
the machines on which a person works are becoming more complicated.

01:31:08.000 --> 01:31:15.000
And so it is necessary to provide a comfortable working environment for a person to work with technology.

01:31:15.000 --> 01:31:19.000
You can make a very complex machine,

01:31:19.000 --> 01:31:22.000
but a person will not know how to use it.

01:31:22.000 --> 01:31:29.000
A person will not know the possibilities that this machine gives him in terms of facilitating his work.

01:31:29.000 --> 01:31:32.000
Therefore, it is necessary to think about ergonomics,

01:31:32.000 --> 01:31:35.000
about how to arrange certain details,

01:31:35.000 --> 01:31:40.000
how not to exaggerate the number of indicators,

01:31:40.000 --> 01:31:44.000
signals that appear in front of a person,

01:31:44.000 --> 01:31:47.000
what he can react to.

01:31:47.000 --> 01:31:51.000
In this regard, it is necessary to talk about the design of the working environment,

01:31:51.000 --> 01:31:54.000
a direct problem associated with organizational behavior.

01:31:54.000 --> 01:32:01.000
I organize and plan connections that arise between different structures of the organization.

01:32:01.000 --> 01:32:05.000
I organize the document turnover that will take place,

01:32:05.000 --> 01:32:09.000
I build a hierarchy and a structure of subordination that will be in the organization,

01:32:10.000 --> 01:32:14.000
and thereby I set the boundaries, the boundaries

01:32:14.000 --> 01:32:19.000
on which the organizational behavior will be implemented.

01:32:19.000 --> 01:32:26.000
Again, the next task is related to the optimization of the relationship between a person and a machine.

01:32:26.000 --> 01:32:32.000
Today's organization is a high-tech organization.

01:32:32.000 --> 01:32:35.000
No matter what you do, you still use a computer,

01:32:35.000 --> 01:32:38.000
you still use a copy machine,

01:32:38.000 --> 01:32:41.000
you use faxes, you use a modem.

01:32:41.000 --> 01:32:48.000
And, accordingly, the effectiveness of your activity depends on the ability to use this equipment.

01:32:48.000 --> 01:32:51.000
Instead of explaining something on the phone for a long time,

01:32:51.000 --> 01:32:56.000
send the necessary data or requests by email,

01:32:56.000 --> 01:33:00.000
and you will not have to explain something on the phone for an hour.

01:33:01.000 --> 01:33:07.000
Using the opportunities that the equipment gives us, the environment,

01:33:07.000 --> 01:33:11.000
is also very important, and this is the task that arises in engineering psychology

01:33:11.000 --> 01:33:14.000
and which naturally determines organizational behavior.

01:33:16.000 --> 01:33:20.000
Well, again, it is very important today, from the point of view of innovation,

01:33:20.000 --> 01:33:24.000
from the point of view of new approaches, to use system technologies.

01:33:25.000 --> 01:33:32.000
It is pointless today, for example, to purchase computers without licensed software.

01:33:32.000 --> 01:33:38.000
You can have the best computers, which have old software products,

01:33:38.000 --> 01:33:47.000
which are low-performance and deprived of all the capabilities that can be used on these computers.

01:33:47.000 --> 01:33:53.000
In this regard, it is necessary to understand the ratio of system qualities.

01:33:53.000 --> 01:33:57.000
I must fully use the technical means,

01:33:57.000 --> 01:33:59.000
when I purchase some complex means.

01:33:59.000 --> 01:34:03.000
This will not only make my life easier, it will make it easier for the functional organization,

01:34:03.000 --> 01:34:08.000
it will increase its efficiency, it will provide it with competitive advantage in the market.

01:34:08.000 --> 01:34:15.000
These are the tasks that are currently under the organizational behavior that it must solve.

01:34:15.000 --> 01:34:20.000
Again, I draw your attention to the fact that these are very specific tasks,

01:34:20.000 --> 01:34:24.000
which have specific outputs, which are measurable.

01:34:24.000 --> 01:34:29.000
And it is precisely organizational behavior that is important,

01:34:29.000 --> 01:34:33.000
because it allows you to solve these tasks and assess the result,

01:34:33.000 --> 01:34:38.000
how effective is the investment of funds in those or other innovations,

01:34:38.000 --> 01:34:44.000
